The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Escape bid with chilli
                                                                                                               Escape bid with chilli
                            
	New Delhi, Oct. 19 (PTI): The man accused of killing journalist Soumya Vishwanathan and call centre executive Jigisha Ghosh today tried to escape from police custody by throwing chilli powder at his minders while being taken to hospital.        
	Ravi Kapoor, the main accused in the murders last year, was caught after the police chased and then fired at him.        
	Ravi was taken to Safdarjung Hospital for a check-up around 11.30am today when he attempted to escape. Assistant sub-inspector Umed Pal, head constable Jagdish and constable Satyapal of the third battalion of the armed police were escorting Ravi. When they went to collect his X-ray report, Ravi threw chilli powder at Pal.        
	Deputy commissioner of police (south) H.G.S. Dhaliwal said: On the way Ravi took out the chilli powder which he had brought surreptitiously and threw at the eyes of ASI Umed Pal. Then he ran away.         
	Dhaliwal said the policemen chased him but could not catch him. Pal fired three rounds but it did not help. The accused was finally captured with the help of Ashok and Virender of Safdarjang Enclave police station, he said.                                                                                                                                                                            
